headline.main: FIFTH ARMY CRACKS FOE'S LINE IN ITALY; British Patrols Reported to Be Nearing Garigliano River -- La Spezia Is Bombed FIFTH ARMY CRACKS FOE'S LINE IN ITALY

lead_paragraph: ALGIERS, Nov. 2 -- Lieut. Gen. Mark W. Clark's Fifth Army has cracked the rocky shell of the German line between Mount Massico and the Matese Ridge and has brought both Venafro and Isernia within artillery range, it was officially announced today.
abstract: 5th Army breaks Ger line between Mt Massico and Matese Ridge; brings Venafro and Isernia within artillery range; Brit units capture Casanova and heights north of Teano; reptd near Garigliano River; Allied fliers bomb northern and central targets and La Spezia on Genoa Gulf
